==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Snapping
<hw>Snap"ping</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <def><pos>a. & n.</pos> from
<er>Snap</er>, <pos>v.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Snapping beetle</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>See
<cref>Snap beetle</cref>, under <er>Snap</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Snapping
turtle</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>A large and
voracious aquatic turtle (<spn>Chelydra serpentina</spn>) common in the
fresh waters of the United States; -- so called from its habit of
seizing its prey by a snap of its jaws. Called also <altname>mud
turtle</altname>.</cd> <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>See <cref>Alligator
snapper</cref>, under <er>Alligator</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snappish</ent>⟦br⟧
